    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-04T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-04T02:00:00-05:00" n="269"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d269">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/204: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-04T09:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 4, 1941—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 5—4:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1896. Personal for Hopkins. With reference to Department’s 604, October 25, 11
                    a.m. [<hi rend="italic">p.m</hi>.], containing your message about lend-lease for
                    Egypt, I am wondering if the reported extension of lend-lease to Turkey<note
                        n="56" xml:id="d269fn56">For correspondence on this subject, see <ref
                            target="#pg_814">pp. 814</ref> ff.</note> indicates an intention to
                    adopt similar measures as regards Egypt. If so is there any data that I can
                    furnish you from this end?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
